As an example, having my computer&#39;s date set to Los Angeles timezone, calling `new Date(&#39;2019-01-15&#39;)` yields the following date: Mon Jan 14 2019 16:00:00 GMT-0800 (Pacific Standard Time)

The Date constructor understands the date string as being UTC time, but calling the getDate, getHours, etc. functions will return the information based on your local timezone.

